com.bt.npm.netrep.npmcommonutils.parser.xml
Class NpmXmlParser

java.lang.Object
  com.bt.npm.netrep.npmcommonutils.parser.xml.NpmXmlParser

public final class NpmXmlParser
extends java.lang.Object

The class uses the NpmXPath implementation to parse the XML using the XPATH or XPathExpression. It has multiple methods which can read one value at a time or multiple values. All the implemented methods accept a reference to the Row object and populates the properties' values in it.

The implementation uses the DOM model, not suitable for parsing very large XML files.

xpathExpressionToColumn

public void xpathExpressionToColumn(java.lang.String xpath,
                                    java.lang.String columnName,
                                    Row row,
                                    int index)
To process the provided xpath(An Expression) and map the result of the node at the given index in the list of nodes. It would use the value of the very first child of the node at the provided index.

Parameters:
xpath - xpath for the field to be read from xml
columnName - the output column name for the CSV
row - Row object to hold the properties' values for CSV output file.
index - index of the node to be selected from the list of node.

multiXpathExpressionToColumns

public java.util.List<Row> multiXpathExpressionToColumns(java.lang.String multiXpath,
                                                         java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> mapXpathToColumns,
                                                         RowConfig rowConfig)
This method is for accessing multiple nodes and populate the values in the ouput Row which is a placeholder for generating the output records in the CSV. The complete Xpath is the combination of the xpath param(multi-node xpath) and the sub-xpaths provided with the map param (mapXpathToColumns).

Parameters:
xpath - : the xpath which required multiple nodes to be fetched
mapXpathToColumns - : contains the input xpaths (keys) which combine with xpath param and set value to the columns provided as values.
row - Row object to hold the properties' values for CSV output file.
index -
